Lewis Thompson Preston (New York, 5 August 1926  Washington, D.C, 4 May 1995) was a U.S. banker. He was President of the World Bank from September 1991 until his death in May 1995. After service in the US Marines during World War II, he graduated from Harvard with a degree in history. He then worked at J. P. Morgan, where he became a board member and then CEO in 1980. 
